description:
&lt;p&gt;Wirral hospital trust is looking for a dynamic, focused professional who is dedicated to meeting quality care delivery through robust surgical site surveillance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exciting opportunity enables the successful candidate to develop and deliver a surveillance programme to meet National and local requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with Infection Prevention and Control and Surgical Specialities, the surveillance programme will incorporate data collection and interpretation that is utilised to inform clinical practice and education and will underpin Wirral hospital Trust Quality Agenda&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Pickstock (Associate Director of Nursing, Trauma and Orthopaedics) sarahpickstock@nhs.net 01516785111 ext 7060&lt;/p&gt;
